        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              I have been accepted to the University of Virginia. They have a <a href="http://www.seas.virginia.edu/acad/programs/producedinva/" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">remote learning program for Engineering Science</a>, specializing in EE/ME/Materials. My specialization would be Mechatronics. <br /><br />While their traditional Engineering programs are ABET accredited, this one is not, and likely will not be, as confirmed by the Director of the program. <br /><br />Now, what kind of risk am I taking if I go down this road and end up with a non-ABET degree? I live in SE Virginia, big Navy area, but there are lots of other employers as well.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
