              Does anyone know what accreditation does for grad school admissions?<br /><br />A PE is a nice discussion, but I got my Masters in my '40s, long after I <span style="font-style: italic">assumed</span> I was done with college.<br /><br />I would certainly hate to learn after the fact that not being accredited for my undergrad blackballed me from any (never mind many) grad schools.<br /><br />The other problem is, today's answer may not be enough.  Sometimes, these things ratchet up over time.<br /><br />Back when my wife was getting into Nursing, not having a bachelor's was no impediment to a fine career.  But, fast forward a couple of decades and now it is.  She no longer qualifies for jobs that her experience certainly qualifies her for.

              

              
              
