              Huh. They have a PE for <a href="http://www.ncees.org/Documents/Public/Exam%20specifications/PE%20Ele%20Computer%20Apr%202009.pdf" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">Computer Engineering</a>?<br /><br />Reading that list made me laugh, that's like a tiny subset of Computer Science taught here. Too bad you can't just sign up for that exam and walk out with the certificate, it doesn't even matter that it's open book, don't have or need it anyway.<br /><br />I guess CE is more focused on the engineering part than the computers one, but damn, the requirements. Basic computer science does not require working under a PE for 4 years, me thinks <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/big_grin.png" alt=":D" title="Big Green" />

              

              
              
            </div>
